            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains the correspondence of Benjamin P. Hinch of New Haven, Ill. A letter from J. T. Lusk discusses the possibility of a trial in order to collect money from a debtor, while a letter from Charles Slocomb is concerned with the possibility of opening a competing mercantile business. There is also a letter from Hinch to his wife in which he informs her of local events in New Haven.</p>
                                 <p>Wilbur Duncan of Decatur, Ill., donated these letters to the Library.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


